## 🟢 Optimal Approach (Two Pointer)

```python
class Solution:
    def maxArea(self, height):
        """
        Optimal: Two Pointer Approach
        Time Complexity: O(n)
        Space Complexity: O(1)
        
        Logic:
        - Start with widest possible gap (i=0, j=n-1)
        - Move pointer with smaller height inward
        - This way we never miss the optimal solution
        """
        res = 0
        n = len(height)
        
        i = 0           # Left pointer
        j = n - 1       # Right pointer
        
        while i < j:
            # Bars BETWEEN i and j
            width = j - i - 1
            
            if height[i] < height[j]:
                # Left bar is smaller, calculate area with left bar
                res = max(res, width * height[i])
                i += 1          # Move left pointer right
                
            elif height[j] < height[i]:
                # Right bar is smaller, calculate area with right bar
                res = max(res, width * height[j])
                j -= 1          # Move right pointer left
                
            else:
                # Both equal, move both pointers
                res = max(res, width * height[i])
                i += 1
                j -= 1
        
        return res
```

