## 💡 Why Two Pointer Works?

```
Key Insight:
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
• We start with maximum possible width
• Area = min(h[i], h[j]) × width
• If we move the LARGER bar inward:
  - Width decreases
  - Height can only be ≤ smaller bar
  - So area definitely decreases
• Therefore: Always move the SMALLER bar
  - Width decreases BUT height might increase
  - This gives chance for better area
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
```
